      <h1 class='title'>Election Guidance</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 21 April 2004 vol 420 c18WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_18ws' title='Col. 18WS &mdash; HC Deb 21 April 2004 vol 420 c18WS' name='column_18ws' href='#column_18ws' rel='bookmark'>18WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0420P2_20040421_CWS_4'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-douglas-alexander' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0420P2_20040421_CWS_4' title='Link to this speech by Mr Douglas Alexander' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-douglas-alexander" title="Mr Douglas Alexander">The Minister for the Cabinet Office and Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster (Mr. Douglas Alexander)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">The Government have today issued guidance to civil servants on the principles which they should observe in relation to the conduct of Government business in the period before the forthcoming elections to the European Parliament, Greater London Authority and to local authorities in England and Wales.</p><p>The guidance stresses that civil servants should conduct themselves in accordance with the civil service code and is based on the need to maintain the political impartiality of the civil service and the need to ensure that public resources are not used for party political purposes.</p><p>The guidance will come into force on Thursday 20 May 2004, ahead of the elections on Thursday 10 June 2004.</p><p>Copies of the guidance have been placed in the Library.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
